      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_425gc' title='Col. 425GC &mdash; HL Deb 29 March 2004 vol 659 c425GC' name='column_425gc' href='#column_425gc' rel='bookmark'>425GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06581'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_313' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 59 [<span class="italic">Regulations</span>]
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06582'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_314' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Evans of Temple Guiting</span> moved Amendment No. 143:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06583'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_315' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 47, line 2, leave out subsection (6).
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06584'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_316' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: In moving Amendment No. 143, I shall speak also to Amendment No. 144.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06585'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_317' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The amendments are a response to the report on the Bill by the Select Committee on Delegated Powers and Regulatory Reform, for which we are grateful. My noble friend Lord Sainsbury of Turville wrote to the noble Lord, Lord Dahrendorf, on 29 January to thank him for the report and to confirm that the Government accepted its recommendations.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06586'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_318' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The amendments will provide that regulations requiring the payment of fees in connection with the regulator's functions made under Clause 54 will be subject to annulment in pursuance of a resolution of either House of Parliament. The Government have accepted that regulations setting fees should be subject to the scrutiny of both Houses. We were persuaded by the fact that regulations setting the fees for Companies House were also subject to the scrutiny of both Houses and felt that that was a logical precedent to follow. I beg to move.
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_426gc' title='Col. 426GC &mdash; HL Deb 29 March 2004 vol 659 c426GC' name='column_426gc' href='#column_426gc' rel='bookmark'>426GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06587'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_319' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06588'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_320' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Evans of Temple Guiting</span> moved Amendment No. 144:
        <q>Page 47, line 5, leave out "or subsection (6) applies to it</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06589'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_321' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06590'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_322' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clause 59, as amended, agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06591'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_323' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Clauses 60 and 61 agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06592'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_324' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 8 [<span class="italic">Repeals</span>]:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06593'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_325' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Sainsbury of Turville</span> moved Amendment No. 145:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06594'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_326' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 70, line 13, leave out "69(4)" and insert "69(2) and (4)"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06595'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_327' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: We realised that, because paragraph 20(a) of Schedule 2 replaces Section 452(1) of the <a href="/acts/companies-act-1985">Companies Act 1985</a>, we should have included in Schedule 8 a repeal of Section 69(2) of the <a href="/acts/companies-act-1989">Companies Act 1989</a>, which amended existing Section 452(1). The amendment will rectify that omission. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06596'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_328' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        On Question, amendment agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06597'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_329' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Schedule 8, as amended, agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06598'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_330' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Remaining clauses agreed to.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06599'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_331' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Bill reported with amendments.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0659P0-06600'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0659P0_20040329_GCR_332' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The Committee adjourned at sixteen minutes past seven o'clock.
      </p>
